location.zh-cn: 美国北卡罗来纳州达勒姆

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学是一所位于美国北卡罗来纳州达勒姆的私立研究型大学，由卫理公会和贵格会于1838年创建。该校被誉为“南方哈佛”，是全球大学高研院联盟及美国大学协会的成员。
description.en: Duke University is a private research university in Durham, North Carolina, founded by Methodists and Quakers in 1838. Known as the 'Harvard of the South', it is a member of the Association of American Universities and other prestigious academic groups.

description.zh-cn: 一个基督新教宗派，与贵格会共同创建了杜克大学的前身。
description.en: A Protestant Christian denomination that, along with the Quakers, founded the institution that would become Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 一个基督教新教派别，与卫理公会共同创建了杜克大学的前身。
description.en: A Protestant Christian denomination that, along with Methodism, founded the institution that would become Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 美国烟草和电力实业家，通过成立杜克捐赠基金，极大地推动了杜克大学的发展。
description.en: American tobacco and electric power industrialist who, through the establishment of The Duke Endowment, greatly advanced the development of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 由詹姆斯·布坎南·杜克于1924年成立的慈善基金会，用于资助杜克大学等机构。
description.en: A charitable foundation established in 1924 by James Buchanan Duke to support institutions including Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 詹姆斯·布坎南·杜克的父亲，杜克大学的命名来源。
description.en: Father of James Buchanan Duke, for whom Duke University is named.

description.zh-cn: 时任三一学院董事长，他坚持将学校更名为杜克大学以感谢杜克家族的慷慨捐赠。
description.en: Then President of Trinity College, he insisted on renaming the school to Duke University to honor the Duke family's generous endowment.

description.zh-cn: 美国第37任总统，杜克大学法学院校友。
description.en: The 37th President of the United States and an alumnus of Duke University School of Law.

description.zh-cn: 苹果公司首席执行官，杜克大学福夸商学院校友。
description.en: CEO of Apple Inc. and an alumnus of Duke University's Fuqua School of Business.

description.zh-cn: 美国慈善家，比尔·盖兹前妻，杜克大学校友。
description.en: American philanthropist, former wife of Bill Gates, and an alumna of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 中国清末民初富商，三一学院（杜克大学前身）的首位外籍学生。
description.en: Chinese businessman in the late Qing dynasty and early Republic of China, and the first international student at Trinity College (the precursor to Duke University).

description.zh-cn: 日本物理学家，波兹曼奖得主，杜克大学博士校友。
description.en: Japanese physicist, Boltzmann Medal recipient, and a PhD alumnus of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 由美国和加拿大顶尖研究型大学组成的协会，杜克大学是其成员之一。
description.en: An association of leading research universities in the United States and Canada, of which Duke University is a member.

description.zh-cn: 美国学者，曾任杜克大学校长。
description.en: American academic who served as the President of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 由杜克大学和新加坡国立大学合作在新加坡建立的研究生医学院。
description.en: A graduate medical school in Singapore established in collaboration between Duke University and the National University of Singapore.

location.zh-cn: 中国江苏省苏州市昆山市

description.zh-cn: 由杜克大学和武汉大学合作创办的中外合作大学，位于中国江苏省昆山市。
description.en: A Sino-American joint venture university founded by Duke University and Wuhan University, located in Kunshan, Jiangsu Province, China.

description.zh-cn: 位于美国北卡罗来纳州的一座城市，是杜克大学的所在地。
description.en: A city in North Carolina, USA, and the location of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学由卫理公会和贵格会于1838年创建。
description.en: Duke University was founded by the Methodist and Quaker communities in 1838.

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学由卫理公会和贵格会于1838年创建。
description.en: Duke University was founded by the Methodist and Quaker communities in 1838.

description.zh-cn: 1924年12月11日，詹姆斯·布坎南·杜克捐赠4千万美元成立了杜克捐赠基金。
description.en: On December 11, 1924, James Buchanan Duke established The Duke Endowment with a $40 million trust fund.

description.zh-cn: 杜克捐赠基金的成立和持续资助，极大地推动了杜克大学（由三一学院更名而来）的发展和扩张。
description.en: The establishment and ongoing funding from The Duke Endowment greatly pushed the development and expansion of Duke University (renamed from Trinity College).

description.zh-cn: 在接受杜克捐赠基金的捐助后，时任三一学院董事长威廉·普莱斯登·富坚持将学校更名为杜克大学，以感谢杜克家族的善举。
description.en: After receiving the endowment from The Duke Endowment, then-President of Trinity College, William Preston Few, insisted on renaming the institution to Duke University to honor the Duke family's philanthropy.

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学更名是为了纪念詹姆斯·布坎南·杜克的父亲华盛顿·杜克及其家族。
description.en: Duke University was renamed in honor of James Buchanan Duke's father, Washington Duke, and his family.

relationships.target: 杜克-新加坡国立大学医学院

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学于2005年在新加坡合作成立了杜克-新加坡国立大学医学院。
description.en: In 2005, Duke University co-founded the Duke-NUS Medical School in Singapore.

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学于2013年在中国苏州合作成立了昆山杜克大学。
description.en: In 2013, Duke University co-founded Duke Kunshan University in Suzhou, China.

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学的前身三一学院于1892年迁至达勒姆，此举对该市的后续发展产生了深远影响。
description.en: Trinity College, the precursor to Duke University, moved to Durham in 1892, a move that has had a profound impact on the city's subsequent development.

description.zh-cn: 杜克大学是美国大学协会（AAU）的成员。
description.en: Duke University is a member of the Association of American Universities (AAU).

description.zh-cn: 理查德·H·布劳德海德曾任杜克大学校长。
description.en: Richard H. Brodhead served as the President of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 理查德·尼克松是杜克大学的知名校友。
description.en: Richard Nixon is a notable alumnus of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 提姆·库克是杜克大学的知名校友。
description.en: Tim Cook is a notable alumnus of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 美琳达·盖兹是杜克大学的知名校友。
description.en: Melinda Gates is a notable alumna of Duke University.

description.zh-cn: 宋嘉澍曾于三一学院（杜克大学前身）求学，是其第一位外籍学生。
description.en: Charlie Soong studied at Trinity College (the precursor to Duke University) and was its first international student.

description.zh-cn: 日本物理学家川崎恭治为杜克大学博士。
description.en: Japanese physicist Kyoji Kawasaki earned his PhD from Duke University.
